TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Valuation of Path Dependent Contracts on the Average
AU  - Ritchken, Peter
AU  - Sankarasubramanian, L.
AU  - Vijh, Anand M.
Y1  - 1993/10/01
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.39.10.1202
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.39.10.1202
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1202
EP  - 1213
VL  - 39
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This article values option contracts based on the average price realized over a finite time horizon. Such contracts are of importance to traders who periodically transact in spot markets and who require protection from adverse moves in their total accrued costs realized over their trading horizons. Explicit valuation models for pricing a variety of path dependent contracts based on geometric and arithmetic averages are developed. The early exercise features of American contracts are investigated, and it is shown that this feature has significant value.
AB  - This article values option contracts based on the average price realized over a finite time horizon. Such contracts are of importance to traders who periodically transact in spot markets and who require protection from adverse moves in their total accrued costs realized over their trading horizons. Explicit valuation models for pricing a variety of path dependent contracts based on geometric and arithmetic averages are developed. The early exercise features of American contracts are investigated, and it is shown that this feature has significant value.
